WEBVTT

00:00.315 --> 00:02.501
A GP for Olivia,
or were you after a specialist?

00:02.814 --> 00:04.014
A psychiatrist, I think.

00:04.045 --> 00:05.744
I want to go home.

00:05.806 --> 00:07.805
Your father and your wife
signed you in.

00:07.806 --> 00:09.805
You cannot leave
without their consent.

00:09.806 --> 00:10.805
Orderlies!

00:10.806 --> 00:11.805
No! No!

00:11.806 --> 00:15.307
Your kind lacks moral fibre, James,
and I'm here to provide it for you.

00:15.308 --> 00:16.828
Is this why you tried
to kill yourself?

00:17.806 --> 00:19.805
It might be best if you had!

00:19.806 --> 00:21.973
I was upset.
You meant it.

00:21.974 --> 00:24.805
I'm not proud.
Nor should you be!

00:24.806 --> 00:25.806
I've just started
drawing up a guest list.

00:25.807 --> 00:28.805
For?
Our engagement party.

00:28.806 --> 00:30.805
I've come to talk about
our daughter.

00:30.806 --> 00:32.973
Who is she?
Anna.

00:32.974 --> 00:35.640
You're that interested in Anna?

00:35.641 --> 00:36.805
I'm being badgered to marry,

00:36.806 --> 00:39.805
and she's the only
vaguely interesting candidate.

00:39.806 --> 00:43.805
I already have investigators at
work, in Paris, London and Berlin.

00:43.806 --> 00:46.973
The talk of the camps.
You were a Jew in France at that time.

00:46.974 --> 00:49.705
I'd rather we concentrate
on the future.

00:49.706 --> 00:51.346
One thing that can be said
for the Nazis -

00:51.383 --> 00:53.206
they kept meticulous records.

